{"questionId":"10697","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Amino acids contain both acidic and basic functional groups.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">An aqueous solution of glutamine contains 0.600 mol dm<sup>−3</sup> of the zwitterion and 0.300 mol dm<sup>−3</sup> of the anionic form.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; pK<sub>a1</sub> = 2.2 and pK<sub>a2</sub> = 9.1</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Calculate the pH of the glutamine solution using section 1 of the data booklet.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">«pH = 9.1 + log&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left[ {\\frac{{0.30}}{{0.60}}} \\right]\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>[</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>0.30</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>0.60</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>]</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> »<br>«= 9.1 + (–0.3)» = 8.8&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"10697","referenceCode":"19M.3.hl.TZ2.10a(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the pH of the glutamine solution using section 1 of the data booklet.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","B: Biochemistry","B.7 Proteins and enzymes (HL only)","Options","B: Biochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}